Internship and Career Guidance
Home
The Department of IT (DIT) aims to secure internship and career opportunities to all undergraduates who diligently follow the Degree programme. The DIT Career Hub provides guidance for DIT students on Internships and future careers. ,The following are some of the activities carried out to this aim:
Organize CV Preparation and Internship Preparation Sessions with the assistance of Industry and Alumni
Organize Mock Interview Sessions for Final Year Undergraduates
Organize Career Fairs for Final Year Undergraduates
Organize career related tech talks with Industry Associations and Alumni
Collaborate with Professional Membership Organizations to promote professionalism in future careers
For Inquiries, please contact
Prof. K.S. Lasith Gunawardena
(Internship Coordinator) or
Ms. Dulari Perera
(Assistant Internship Coordinator).
Information for current Interns (4th Year, 2025)
Internship Registry
(Companies who have provided internship for DIT Students in the past)
Internship Introduction Letter Requesting form
(To receive a letter signed by Head, Department of IT supporting your internship request aimed at a particular organization)

Employability Skill Development

Maximise Your Employability
Employability is the achievement of ‚Äúthe skills, understandings and personal attributes that make an individual¬†more likely to secure employment and be successful in their chosen occupations to the benefit of¬†themselves, the workforce, the community and the economy‚Äù (Yorke, 2006), (p.8).
University life isn‚Äôt just lectures and assessments. Extracurricular activities are a great way to boost your CV, broaden your mind, make new friends and have fun.¬†The Department, the Faculty, the University, and students organize numerous extra-curricular activities.¬†Explore career opportunities, develop employability skills by joining¬† a club/sociaty.

Employment Opportunities and Professional Links
Home
About
Employment Opportunities
Graduates of this degree programme have two main avenues to choose for their career paths. They can decide either to select information systems field or to select the general management field. Graduates who opt for a career in information systems can expect to commence his/her career in a position such as
Business Analyst, Systems Analyst, IS Manager, IT/ERP Consultant, Quality Assurance Manager or Project Manager
. With further enhancements of Information Technology related knowledge and skills, a graduate can focus on positions such as
Software Engineer, Database Administrator and Network Administrator
.
Graduates who are willing a career in general management can find job positions in any of the functional areas such as
Accounting, Marketing, Finance, Human Resource Management, Production Operations Management
etc. Their skills in logical thinking, problem solving and IT applications should help them to perform better than others in those positions. Further studies in the relevant filed and other professional qualifications will support their career enhancement and personal development in the long run.
Professional Links
The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Microsoft Sri Lanka (Pvt) Ltd., which has enabled the Department to get the membership of the Microsoft Developer Network Academic Alliance Programme. Under this programme, students of the department are provided with selected Microsoft Software free of charge for research purposes. The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Providence Network and Solutions too which has enabled us to get the ‚Äúabas‚Äù ERP software free of charge for the department.
Furthermore, an MoU was signed with one of the world‚Äôs largest software solutions providers ‚Äì Virtusa Corporation in 2023 which enables graduates to benefit from a Global company. Students also have access to the Oracle Academy, enabling them to follow certifications from Oracle Free of Charge. The
department and it‚Äôs staff also maintains close links with professional and industry associations in IT including Sri Lanka Association for Software and Services Companies (SLASSCOM), Computer Society of Sri Lanka (CSSL), ISACA Sri Lanka Chapter, PMI Sri Lanka Chapter, IIBA Colombo Chapter, IEEE Sri Lanka Section, ISC2 Colombo Chapter, and BCS Sri Lanka Section, which has allowed department students to be exposed to programs conducted by these organizations as well as get experiences from industry professionals.
Employment Opportunity News
Global Tech Giant Virtusa signs MoU with DIT
Posted: August 11, 2023
Virtusa Corporation stands as a global beacon in the realm of information technology services. This company is dedicated to delivering unparalleled digital engineering and technological solutions to enterprises spanning a wide array of industries worldwide, including financial services, healthcare, communications, media, entertainment, travel, manufacturing, and technology. With an impressive global workforce exceeding 35,000 employees, Virtusa [‚Ä¶]
Fostering Industry-Academia Collaboration with Aeturnum for Enhanced IT Education
Posted: July 28, 2023
Aeturnum is a Software Solutions provided headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts, USA that offers a full range of IT services under compressing delivery timeframes, offering its customers complete end-to-end business and technology solutions with a diverse range of technical expertise and in-depth domain knowledge combining the right people and cutting edge technologies. Representatives from Aeturnum Lanka [‚Ä¶]

Alumni Association

Welcome to the Alumni Association of the Department of Information Technology (DITAA)
The Alumni Association of the Department of Information Technology (DITAA) is a vibrant community that bridges the past, present, and future of the Department of Information Technology, Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce, at the University of Sri Jayewardenepura. Established with the vision of fostering lifelong connections among alumni and between alumni and the department, DITAA serves as a platform for collaboration, knowledge sharing, and mutual growth.
Our mission is to strengthen the bonds between the university and its graduates, promote professional and personal development, and contribute to the advancement of the department. Through a diverse range of programs, including networking events, mentorship opportunities, and skill development initiatives, DITAA actively engages alumni from various batches and professional backgrounds.
What We Offer:
Networking Opportunities:
Reconnect with former classmates and expand your professional network through regular meetups, online platforms, and social events.
Mentorship Programs:
Guide and inspire current students by sharing your professional expertise and career insights.
Career Support:
Access exclusive job opportunities, industry insights, and resources to help you excel in your career.
Knowledge Sharing:
Participate in workshops, webinars, and conferences organized by the association to stay updated on the latest trends and technologies.
Giving Back:
Contribute to the development of the department through scholarships, funding for research, and volunteering opportunities.
DITAA is not just an association; it is a testament to the enduring spirit of camaraderie and excellence that defines our alumni. We invite all graduates to join us in this journey of shared success and to play an active role in shaping the future of our department and the IT community at large.

Join Us
If you are an alumnus of the Department of Information Technology, we encourage you to become a member of DITAA. Together, let us celebrate our achievements, support one another, and contribute to the greater good.

About S@IT
Home
Students‚Äô Association of Information Technology (S@IT) is the student body affiliated to the Department of Information Technology established in 2003. The association carries out various academic and social activities such as arranging seminars, workshops, field visits and student get-together to develop knowledge, skills and research abilities of students.
Objectives of the S@IT:
To facilitate the career development of the members of S@IT.
Providing welfare facilities to the members of S@IT.
Encourage members in the involvement of communal activities.
To build and maintain a sound relationship with cooperate sector.
To uplift the quality and value of research and training of members of S@IT.
To encourage and facilitate students to actively participate in information technology related activities.

Welcome to the Department of Information Technology
The information systems discipline focuses on the use and the application of information and communications technologies (ICT) in the government, business and the society. Knowledge¬†about information systems is now regarded as a core literacy requirement in the modern business environment. In addition, a very good understanding of the capabilities, issues and the risks associated with information systems is demanded as an essential skill for almost all managerial positions in the modern workplace.¬† Succeeding as an innovative manager the understanding of how and where to use information systems, communications technology and knowledge management strategies are essential. These skills are not negotiable for modern businesses.
The Department of Information Technology is committed to prepare students with the applied technology, core business and communication skills needed to compete in a technology-driven corporate world. The Department offers a globally competitive four-year special degree in Business Information Systems. The degree provides an opportunity to enhance knowledge of information technology and business management practices in order to lead technical initiatives within an organization.

Executive Committee
Research
Exploration
Welcome to the Department of Information Technology
The information systems discipline focuses on the use and the application of information and communications technologies (ICT) in the government, business and the society. Knowledge¬†about information systems is now regarded as a core literacy requirement in the modern business environment. In addition, a very good understanding of the capabilities, issues and the risks associated with information systems is demanded as an essential skill for almost all managerial positions in the modern workplace.¬† Succeeding as an innovative manager the understanding of how and where to use information systems, communications technology and knowledge management strategies are essential. These skills are not negotiable for modern businesses.
The Department of Information Technology is committed to prepare students with the applied technology, core business and communication skills needed to compete in a technology-driven corporate world. The Department offers a globally competitive four-year special degree in Business Information Systems. The degree provides an opportunity to enhance knowledge of information technology and business management practices in order to lead technical initiatives within an organization.

Introduction to the Department
Home
About
Introduction
T
he rapid development in Information Technology (IT) has enabled business organizations to exploit IT as a tool to obtain competitive advantages. A key ingredient in the formula for success in this endeavour is for business professionals to apply Information Technology in management practices. Graduates armed with appropriate knowledge in Management and Information Technology disciplines is desired by the industry to meet the national requirement. The launch of a new Special degree programme named B.Sc. in Business Administration (Information Systems) (Special) by the Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce, University of Sri Jayewardenepura in 2001 was aimed to meet this demand. This programme was the first of its kind in Sri Lanka that combined Management and Information Technology disciplines for students in the Advanced Level commerce stream. The Department of Information Technology and Decision Sciences was established in the Faculty to provide the organizational infrastructure for the degree programme.
In December 2007, the Department was split into two separate departments ‚Äì namely Information Technology and Decision Sciences to facilitate the development of the separate disciplines. Subsequently, the existing degree programme offered by the Department of Information Technology was renamed as B.Sc. in Business Information Systems (Special) Degree. The renaming of the degree was carried out to better reflect the composition of the course structure and to address the evolving market needs.
Top Story
BISSS 2025: Sixth BIS Student Symposium
Posted: February 18, 2025
The Sixth BIS Student Symposium (BISSS 2025), organized by the Department of Information Technology, was held on Wednesday, February 18, 2025, from 1:00 PM onwards at SBFF 01 & 02 Halls, Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce, University of Sri Jayewardenepura. The symposium provided a platform for students to share their research findings and fresh [‚Ä¶]
Facilities at the Department
The department is located at the Soratha Building of the university. The department office is equipped with necessary infrastructure,¬†computer lab, furniture, and other equipment to provide support to both lecturers and students of the department. Each staff member has his/her room with necessary facilities for studying, research, and meeting with students. Students have a resource centre which they use for group activities, and also for various activities performed by their Students‚Äô Association.
Practical Training
Practical training is a compulsory component in the degree program. Students are allowed to go for practical training during the final year of their degree programme. The aim of the practical training is to expose students to a working environment so that they can gain variety of benefits that include: gaining know-how, developing skills and abilities, gaining work experience, and applying theoretical knowledge in to practice.

Employment Opportunities and Professional Links
Home
About
Employment Opportunities
Graduates of this degree programme have two main avenues to choose for their career paths. They can decide either to select information systems field or to select the general management field. Graduates who opt for a career in information systems can expect to commence his/her career in a position such as
Business Analyst, Systems Analyst, IS Manager, IT/ERP Consultant, Quality Assurance Manager or Project Manager
. With further enhancements of Information Technology related knowledge and skills, a graduate can focus on positions such as
Software Engineer, Database Administrator and Network Administrator
.
Graduates who are willing a career in general management can find job positions in any of the functional areas such as
Accounting, Marketing, Finance, Human Resource Management, Production Operations Management
etc. Their skills in logical thinking, problem solving and IT applications should help them to perform better than others in those positions. Further studies in the relevant filed and other professional qualifications will support their career enhancement and personal development in the long run.
Professional Links
The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Microsoft Sri Lanka (Pvt) Ltd., which has enabled the Department to get the membership of the Microsoft Developer Network Academic Alliance Programme. Under this programme, students of the department are provided with selected Microsoft Software free of charge for research purposes. The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Providence Network and Solutions too which has enabled us to get the ‚Äúabas‚Äù ERP software free of charge for the department.
Furthermore, an MoU was signed with one of the world‚Äôs largest software solutions providers ‚Äì Virtusa Corporation in 2023 which enables graduates to benefit from a Global company. Students also have access to the Oracle Academy, enabling them to follow certifications from Oracle Free of Charge. The
department and it‚Äôs staff also maintains close links with professional and industry associations in IT including Sri Lanka Association for Software and Services Companies (SLASSCOM), Computer Society of Sri Lanka (CSSL), ISACA Sri Lanka Chapter, PMI Sri Lanka Chapter, IIBA Colombo Chapter, IEEE Sri Lanka Section, ISC2 Colombo Chapter, and BCS Sri Lanka Section, which has allowed department students to be exposed to programs conducted by these organizations as well as get experiences from industry professionals.

This company is dedicated to delivering unparalleled digital engineering and technological solutions to enterprises spanning a wide array of industries worldwide, including financial services, healthcare, communications, media, entertainment, travel, manufacturing, and technology. BSc Honours in Business Information Systems Degree (Effective from 2022)
Home
Study
Aims/Objectives of the Degree Programme
This degree programme is focused to provide sound theoretical and practical knowledge in the two disciplines of Management and Information Systems. By combining these two prominent disciplines, this programme will equip the students with cutting edge business management skills as well as information systems skills to work, manage and succeed in any business. This programme has been especially designed to meet the aspirations of students who are willing and seeking a career either in Management or in Information Systems fields.
Graduate Profile
A student who has successfully completed the BSc Honours in Business Information Systems degree will be a unique graduate who will possess a high level of knowledge in both management and information systems domains. They will be distinguished from others for their diversified knowledge, their generic skills and technical skills, their attitude, flexibility and adaptability, and their desire for continuous learning over a lifelong career, making them an ideal choice for today‚Äôs dynamic and flexible organizations.
Graduate Attributes
The attributes of a BSc Honours in BIS graduate is based around four main domains of learning, as highlighted below. They represent the clusters of generic capabilities which the department seeks to foster in all graduates through the teaching and learning experiences of its degree programme.
Knowledge:
BIS graduates will have in-depth subject and practical knowledge in the fields of Management and Information Systems which can be applied in both local and global contexts.
Skills:
BIS graduates will develop a variety of generic skills which will be useful in starting their career and also in their career advancement.
Attitudes, Values, Professionalism, and Vision for life:
BIS graduates will develop right thinking, behaviour, practices, and goals for the future.
Mind-set and Paradigm:
BIS graduates will have a commitment to the on-going acquisition of new knowledge and new skills and they are expected to be lifelong learners.
Programme Structure for Years I, II, III and IV
The curriculum of the Bachelor of Science Honours in Business Information Systems degree has been designed to meet the requirement of SLQF Level 6. The study programme consists of 127 credits and it includes both an internship training programme and a research study. The programme covers four academic years of learning. An academic year consists of two semesters.
All undergraduate students enrolled in the Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce are required to follow a common curriculum in management in the first two semesters of study. This is intended to provide the core business knowledge by teaching basic concepts in all functional areas in business.

Employment Opportunities
Graduates of this degree programme have two main avenues to choose for their career paths. They can decide either to select information systems field or to select the general management field. Graduates who opt for a career in information systems can expect to commence his/her career in a position such as Business Analyst, Systems Analyst, IS Manager, IT/ERP Consultant, Quality Assurance Manager or Project Manager. With further enhancements of Information Technology related knowledge and skills, a graduate can focus on positions such as Software Engineer, Database Administrator and Network Administrator.
Graduates who are willing a career in general management can find job positions in any of the functional areas such as Accounting, Marketing, Finance, Human Resource Management, Production Operations Management etc. Their skills in logical thinking, problem solving and IT applications should help them to perform better than others in those positions. Further studies in the relevant filed and other professional qualifications will support their career enhancement and personal development in the long run.
Professional Links
The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Microsoft Sri Lanka (Pvt) Ltd., which has enabled the Department to get the membership of the Microsoft Developer Network Academic Alliance Programme. Under this programme, students of the department are provided with selected Microsoft Software free of charge for research purposes. The department was signed a Memorandum of Understanding
with one of the world‚Äôs largest software solutions providers ‚Äì Virtusa Corporation in 2023 which enables graduates to benefit from a Global company. Students also have access to the Oracle Academy, enabling them to follow certifications from Oracle Free of Charge. The
department and it‚Äôs staff also maintains close links with professional and industry associations in IT including Sri Lanka Association for Software and Services Companies (SLASSCOM), Computer Society of Sri Lanka (CSSL), ISACA Sri Lanka Chapter, PMI Sri Lanka Chapter, IIBA Colombo Chapter, IEEE Sri Lanka Section, ISC2 Colombo Chapter, and BCS Sri Lanka Section, which has allowed department students to be exposed to programs conducted by these organizations as well as get experiences from industry professionals.

B.Sc. in Business Information Systems (Special) Degree
Home
Study
Aims/Objectives of the Degree Programme
This degree programme is focused to provide sound theoretical and practical knowledge in the two disciplines of Management and Information Systems. By combining these two prominent disciplines, this programme will equip the students with cutting edge business management skills as well as information systems skills to work, manage and succeed in any business. This programme has been specially designed to meet the aspirations of students who are willing and seeking a career either in Management or in Information Systems fields.
Graduate Profile
A student who has successfully completed the B.Sc. in Business Information Systems degree will be a unique graduate who will possess a high level of knowledge in both management and information systems domains. They will be distinguished from others for their diversified knowledge, their generic skills and technical skills, their attitude, flexibility and adaptability, and their desire for continuous learning over a lifelong career, making them an ideal choice for today‚Äôs dynamic and flexible organizations.
Graduate Attributes
The attributes of a B.Sc. in BIS graduate is based around four main domains of learning, as highlighted below. They represent the clusters of generic capabilities which the study programme seeks to foster in all graduates through the teaching and learning experiences of its study programme.
Knowledge:
BIS graduates will have in-depth subject and practical knowledge in the fields of Management and Information Systems which can be applied in both local and global contexts.
Skills:
BIS graduates will develop a variety of generic skills which will be useful in starting their career and also in their career advancement.
Attitudes, Values, Professionalism, and Vision for life:
BIS graduates will develop right thinking, behaviour, practices, and goals for the future.
Mind-set and Paradigm:
BIS graduates will have a commitment to the on-going acquisition of new knowledge and new skills and they are expected to be lifelong learners.

Employment Opportunities
Graduates of this degree programme have two main avenues to choose for their career paths. They can decide either to select information systems field or to select the general management field. Graduates who opt for a career in information systems can expect to commence his/her career in a position such as Business Analyst, Systems Analyst, IS Manager, IT/ERP Consultant, Quality Assurance Manager or Project Manager. With further enhancements of Information Technology related knowledge and skills, a graduate can focus on positions such as Software Engineer, Database Administrator and Network Administrator.
Graduates who are willing a career in general management can find job positions in any of the functional areas such as Accounting, Marketing, Finance, Human Resource Management, Production Operations Management etc. Their skills in logical thinking, problem solving and IT applications should help them to perform better than others in those positions. Further studies in the relevant filed and other professional qualifications will support their career enhancement and personal development in the long run.
Professional Links
The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Microsoft Sri Lanka (Pvt) Ltd., which has enabled the Department to get the membership of the Microsoft Developer Network Academic Alliance Programme. Under this programme, students of the department are provided with selected Microsoft Software free of charge for research purposes. The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Providence Network and Solutions too which has enabled us to get the ‚Äúabas‚Äù ERP software free of charge for the department. The department also maintains close links with several other private sector organizations, which has allowed the department to nominate selected students for industrial placement. Links have also been established with the key Professional Associations which are related to IT Industry.

About this Event
The sixth ‚ÄúBIS Student Symposium‚Äù organized by the Department of Information Technology will be held on Tuesday, the 18th of February 2025¬†starting from 1.00 pm onwards at SBFF1 Hall,¬†Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce, University of Sri Jayewardenepura. The event is organized with the objective of providing the students a platform to engage, showcase and contemplate on the more socially conscious and applied avenues of Information Systems and Management education.
The symposium will consist of 2 main tracks showcasing extended abstracts and projects presented by the undergraduates of the department. The event will be conducted with the participation of undergraduates, university academic staff members and practitioners of the industry.
We look forward to seeing you all on the 18th!

Postdoctoral Researcher at ETH Zurich, Switzerland Incoming Research Scientist at Nokia Bell Labs, UK

Internship and Career Guidance
Home
The Department of IT (DIT) aims to secure internship and career opportunities to all undergraduates who diligently follow the Degree programme. The DIT Career Hub provides guidance for DIT students on Internships and future careers. ,The following are some of the activities carried out to this aim:
Organize CV Preparation and Internship Preparation Sessions with the assistance of Industry and Alumni
Organize Mock Interview Sessions for Final Year Undergraduates
Organize Career Fairs for Final Year Undergraduates
Organize career related tech talks with Industry Associations and Alumni
Collaborate with Professional Membership Organizations to promote professionalism in future careers
For Inquiries, please contact
Prof. K.S. Lasith Gunawardena
(Internship Coordinator) or
Ms. Dulari Perera
(Assistant Internship Coordinator).
Information for current Interns (4th Year, 2025)
Internship Registry
(Companies who have provided internship for DIT Students in the past)
Internship Introduction Letter Requesting form
(To receive a letter signed by Head, Department of IT supporting your internship request aimed at a particular organization)

Maximise Your Employability
Employability is the achievement of ‚Äúthe skills, understandings and personal attributes that make an individual¬†more likely to secure employment and be successful in their chosen occupations to the benefit of¬†themselves, the workforce, the community and the economy‚Äù (Yorke, 2006), (p.8).
University life isn‚Äôt just lectures and assessments. Extracurricular activities are a great way to boost your CV, broaden your mind, make new friends and have fun.¬†The Department, the Faculty, the University, and students organize numerous extra-curricular activities.¬†Explore career opportunities, develop employability skills by joining¬† a club/sociaty.

Employment Opportunities and Professional Links
Home
About
Employment Opportunities
Graduates of this degree programme have two main avenues to choose for their career paths. They can decide either to select information systems field or to select the general management field. Graduates who opt for a career in information systems can expect to commence his/her career in a position such as
Business Analyst, Systems Analyst, IS Manager, IT/ERP Consultant, Quality Assurance Manager or Project Manager
. With further enhancements of Information Technology related knowledge and skills, a graduate can focus on positions such as
Software Engineer, Database Administrator and Network Administrator
.
Graduates who are willing a career in general management can find job positions in any of the functional areas such as
Accounting, Marketing, Finance, Human Resource Management, Production Operations Management
etc. Their skills in logical thinking, problem solving and IT applications should help them to perform better than others in those positions. Further studies in the relevant filed and other professional qualifications will support their career enhancement and personal development in the long run.
Professional Links
The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Microsoft Sri Lanka (Pvt) Ltd., which has enabled the Department to get the membership of the Microsoft Developer Network Academic Alliance Programme. Under this programme, students of the department are provided with selected Microsoft Software free of charge for research purposes. The department has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Providence Network and Solutions too which has enabled us to get the ‚Äúabas‚Äù ERP software free of charge for the department.
Furthermore, an MoU was signed with one of the world‚Äôs largest software solutions providers ‚Äì Virtusa Corporation in 2023 which enables graduates to benefit from a Global company. Students also have access to the Oracle Academy, enabling them to follow certifications from Oracle Free of Charge. The
department and it‚Äôs staff also maintains close links with professional and industry associations in IT including Sri Lanka Association for Software and Services Companies (SLASSCOM), Computer Society of Sri Lanka (CSSL), ISACA Sri Lanka Chapter, PMI Sri Lanka Chapter, IIBA Colombo Chapter, IEEE Sri Lanka Section, ISC2 Colombo Chapter, and BCS Sri Lanka Section, which has allowed department students to be exposed to programs conducted by these organizations as well as get experiences from industry professionals.
Employment Opportunity News
Global Tech Giant Virtusa signs MoU with DIT
Posted: August 11, 2023
Virtusa Corporation stands as a global beacon in the realm of information technology services. This company is dedicated to delivering unparalleled digital engineering and technological solutions to enterprises spanning a wide array of industries worldwide, including financial services, healthcare, communications, media, entertainment, travel, manufacturing, and technology. With an impressive global workforce exceeding 35,000 employees, Virtusa [‚Ä¶]
Fostering Industry-Academia Collaboration with Aeturnum for Enhanced IT Education
Posted: July 28, 2023
Aeturnum is a Software Solutions provided headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts, USA that offers a full range of IT services under compressing delivery timeframes, offering its customers complete end-to-end business and technology solutions with a diverse range of technical expertise and in-depth domain knowledge combining the right people and cutting edge technologies. Representatives from Aeturnum Lanka [‚Ä¶]

Alumni Association
Home
Welcome to the Alumni Association of the Department of Information Technology (DITAA)
The Alumni Association of the Department of Information Technology (DITAA) is a vibrant community that bridges the past, present, and future of the Department of Information Technology, Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce, at the University of Sri Jayewardenepura. Established with the vision of fostering lifelong connections among alumni and between alumni and the department, DITAA serves as a platform for collaboration, knowledge sharing, and mutual growth.
Our mission is to strengthen the bonds between the university and its graduates, promote professional and personal development, and contribute to the advancement of the department. Through a diverse range of programs, including networking events, mentorship opportunities, and skill development initiatives, DITAA actively engages alumni from various batches and professional backgrounds.
What We Offer:
Networking Opportunities:
Reconnect with former classmates and expand your professional network through regular meetups, online platforms, and social events.
Mentorship Programs:
Guide and inspire current students by sharing your professional expertise and career insights.
Career Support:
Access exclusive job opportunities, industry insights, and resources to help you excel in your career.
Knowledge Sharing:
Participate in workshops, webinars, and conferences organized by the association to stay updated on the latest trends and technologies.
Giving Back:
Contribute to the development of the department through scholarships, funding for research, and volunteering opportunities.
DITAA is not just an association; it is a testament to the enduring spirit of camaraderie and excellence that defines our alumni. We invite all graduates to join us in this journey of shared success and to play an active role in shaping the future of our department and the IT community at large.

Join Us
If you are an alumnus of the Department of Information Technology, we encourage you to become a member of DITAA. Together, let us celebrate our achievements, support one another, and contribute to the greater good.

About S@IT
Home
Students‚Äô Association of Information Technology (S@IT) is the student body affiliated to the Department of Information Technology established in 2003. The association carries out various academic and social activities such as arranging seminars, workshops, field visits and student get-together to develop knowledge, skills and research abilities of students.
Objectives of the S@IT:
To facilitate the career development of the members of S@IT.
Providing welfare facilities to the members of S@IT.
Encourage members in the involvement of communal activities.
To build and maintain a sound relationship with cooperate sector.
To uplift the quality and value of research and training of members of S@IT.
To encourage and facilitate students to actively participate in information technology related activities.

The opportunities available to improve language skills

Department of English Language Teaching (DELT):
The DELT provides structured certificate and diploma programs in English, designed to enhance listening, speaking, reading, and writing skills. These courses are open to both internal students and external participants.
These programs focus on practical language use, including functional grammar, vocabulary, oral skills, and even language through literature.
Compulsory English Courses:
The university includes compulsory English courses within its degree programs which is conducted by BCC Unit, ensuring that students develop a baseline level of English proficiency.
Regular workshops and seminars on communication skills may be organized by various faculties. These can include public speaking, presentation skills, debate, and creative writing.

How to find relevant reference materials for the subject

Course Materials
Lecture Notes & Slides: Check if the lecturer provides course materials on LMS.
Recommended Textbooks: Related textbooks and other reference materials will be provided by your lecturer. These books can often be found in the library or through online bookstores.

Past Exam Papers: Exam papers from previous years can be a great reference to understand the types of topics covered. You may find these in the university library for past papers.
Physical Books and Journals: Visit the University Library to explore physical reference materials like books, journals, and research papers related to your subject. University libraries typically have a wide range of textbooks and academic publications.

Online Databases and Repositories
Google Scholar: Use Google Scholar to find peer-reviewed articles, theses, books, and conference papers. It‚Äôs an excellent tool for locating academic research and reference materials.
ResearchGate: This platform connects researchers and provides access to a wide range of publications, articles, and academic papers. You can also directly contact authors to request copies of their papers if needed.


The scholarships available to go abroad after completing degree?
General Scholarship Sources:

Government Scholarships:
Many countries offer scholarships to international students. Examples include:
Fulbright Scholarships (USA): These are highly competitive scholarships for graduate study, research, or teaching. ¬† 
Chevening Scholarships (UK): These scholarships are awarded to outstanding emerging leaders to pursue master's degrees in the UK. ¬† 
Japanese Government (MEXT) Scholarships: The Japanese Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology offers scholarships to international students. ¬† 
Australian Government Scholarships: Australia provides various scholarships, such as Australia Awards Scholarships. ¬† 
It's crucial to check the websites of the respective country's embassies or high commissions in Sri Lanka for detailed information.
University-Specific Scholarships:
Many universities worldwide offer scholarships to international postgraduate students.
These scholarships may be based on academic merit, research potential, or specific fields of study.
It's essential to visit the websites of universities you're interested in and explore their scholarship opportunities.
International Organizations and Foundations:
Organizations like the United Nations and various private foundations offer scholarships for international students. ¬† 
Ministry of Higher Education, Sri Lanka:
The Sri lankan ministry of higher education also provides information regarding scholarships.

 Therefore it is a very valuable resource. 

The other higher educational qualifications  BIS gaduates can obtain after first degree

Potential Postgraduate Paths:
Master's Degrees:
Master of Business Administration (MBA): This is a very common choice, allowing BIS graduates to enhance their management and leadership skills.
Master of Science (MSc) in Information Technology: Specializing in areas like cybersecurity, data science, or software engineering. ¬† 
MSc in Management Information Systems (MIS): A more focused postgraduate degree that deepens their understanding of information systems within a business context.
MSc in Data Science or Business Analytics: As data becomes increasingly important, these programs are highly relevant.
Postgraduate Diplomas:
Postgraduate diplomas in related fields like IT, management, or project management can provide specialized skills in a shorter timeframe. ¬† 
Research Degrees:
MPhil (Master of Philosophy) and PhD programs: For those interested in academic or research careers. ¬† 


Available postgraduate courses in University of Sri Jayawardenepura 

Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce:
This faculty offers a wide range of postgraduate programs that are highly relevant to BIS graduates. These include:
Master of Business Administration (MBA):
A very popular choice for BIS graduates looking to enhance their management and leadership skills.
Master of Science (MSc) in Management:
Provides advanced knowledge in various management disciplines.
MSc in Applied Finance:
For those interested in the financial aspects of business and IT.
MSc in Marketing:
For those that want to enhance their marketing skills in a modern digital landscape.
Other Masters programs such as:
Master of Public Management ¬† 
Master of Business Economics ¬† 
¬† 
It is important to check the Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce website, as they offer postgraduate diplomas as well. ¬† 
Faculty of Applied Sciences:
This faculty offers postgraduate programs in Computer Science, which is a natural progression for BIS graduates.
Master of Science in Computer Science:
Allows for specialization in areas like software engineering, data science, and cybersecurity.
¬† 
Where to find detailed information:

University of Sri Jayewardenepura's official website:
Specifically, the websites of the Faculty of Management Studies and Commerce and the Faculty of Applied Sciences. ¬† 
Faculty of Graduate Studies:
This faculty provides comprehensive information on all postgraduate programs offered by the university.

The professional  cources that I should follow  to be a Software Engineer/ Data Scientist/ Business Analyst/ Quality Assurance Engineer


Software Engineer:

Programming Certifications:
Oracle Certified Java Programmer: Demonstrates proficiency in Java, a widely used language.
Microsoft Certified: Azure Developer Associate: Focuses on cloud-based development using Microsoft Azure. ¬† 
AWS Certified Developer - Associate: Validates skills in developing AWS applications. ¬† 
Python certifications: There are many Python certifications that focus on web development (Django, Flask) or general purpose python. ¬† 
Web Development Courses:
Full-stack development courses focusing on technologies like JavaScript (React, Angular, Node.js), HTML, CSS, and databases.
DevOps Certifications:
Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA): Essential for containerization and orchestration.
AWS Certified DevOps Engineer - Professional: For advanced DevOps skills on AWS.
Cybersecurity Certifications:
While not always required, cybersecurity knowledge is increasingly valuable. Certifications like CompTIA Security+ or Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH) can be beneficial. ¬† 


Data Scientist:
Data Science Certifications:
IBM Data Science Professional Certificate: Covers essential data science skills.
Microsoft Certified: Azure Data Scientist Associate: Focuses on data science on the Azure platform. ¬† 
Statistical Analysis and Machine Learning Courses:
Courses focusing on Python libraries like scikit-learn, pandas, and NumPy. ¬† 
Deep learning courses using TensorFlow or PyTorch. ¬† 
Data Visualization Tools:
Courses on tools like Tableau or Power BI. ¬† 
Big Data Technologies:
Courses on Hadoop, Spark, and related technologies. ¬† 

Business Analyst:
Business Analysis Certifications:
Certified Business Analysis Professional (CBAP): A globally recognized certification.
IIBA Entry Certificate in Business Analysis (ECBA): For those starting their career.
Project Management Courses:
Project Management Professional (PMP): Helpful for managing projects and requirements.
Agile and Scrum Certifications: Agile methodologies are widely used.
Data Analysis and SQL:
Courses that improve SQL skills, and data understanding.
Business Intelligence (BI) Tools:
Familiarity with tools like Power BI, Tableau, or similar.

Quality Assurance Engineer:
Software Testing Certifications:
ISTQB (International Software Testing Qualifications Board) Certifications: A widely recognized standard. ¬† 
Certified Software Tester (CSTE): Another valuable certification.
Automation Testing Tools:
Courses on tools like Selenium, JUnit, or TestComplete.
Performance Testing:
Courses on tools like JMeter or LoadRunner.
API Testing:
Learning tools like Postman.

Elective courses would you recommend for someone aiming to specialize in software engineering
Year 3 Semester 1 (Elective courses)
ITC 3373 Object Oriented Programming:
This is fundamental to modern software development.
ITC 3375 Software Engineering:
This course directly addresses the principles and practices of software development.

Year 3 Semester 2  (Elective courses)

ITC 3380 Programming Applications and Frameworks:
This will help you learn the practical application of programming in real world scenarios.
ITC 3381 Software Quality Assurance:
This is very important to software developement, and can be a career path on its own.

Year 4 Semester 1  (Elective courses)
ITC 4375 Artificial Intelligence Applications:
suggests a focus on the practical use of AI, which is highly valuable for a software engineer
ITC 4374 Virtualization and Cloud Computing:
Most software today is built and deployed in cloud environments.


Year 4 Semester 2  
Research Areas  
Artificial Intelligence in Software Engineering:
Focus:
Developing AI-powered tools for code analysis, testing, and debugging.
Exploring machine learning for software quality assurance  (including Deep learning ,Reinforcement Learning)
Researching AI-driven automation in software development.
Relevance:
AI is transforming software development processes. ¬† 
AI skills are highly sought after.

Related Core Subjects (Years 1-4):
These core subjects provide a foundation for a Software Engineering career:
Year 1:
ITC 1370 Information Technology for Business:
Provides a foundational understanding of IT concepts.
ITC 1171 Computational Thinking for Problem Solving:
Develops essential problem-solving skills crucial for programming.
Year 2:
ITC 2370 Computer Programming:
Essential programming skills are introduced.
ITC 2373 Database Design and Development:
Databases are integral to most software applications.
ITC 2374 Systems Analysis and Design:
This course teaches the process of planning and designing software systems.
ITC 2375 Web-based Application Development:
Very important for modern software developement.
Year 3:
ITC 3370 Information Technology Infrastructure:
Understanding the underlying infrastructure is crucial for software deployment.
Year 4:
ITC 4671 Information Systems Development Research Project:
Provides an opportunity for in-depth software development experience.
ITC 4372 Professional Ethics and ICT Law:
Understanding the legal and ethical side of software development is very important.
Elective courses would you recommend for someone aiming to specialize in business analysis
ITC 4378 Advanced Business Analytics:
Why: Building upon basic data analysis, this course dives deeper into advanced analytical techniques and tools. This is very important for a modern Business Analyst, due to the high volume of data that companies now have.
ITC 4372 Professional Ethics and ICT Law:
Why: Business analysts work with sensitive information and must adhere to ethical standards and legal regulations. This course helps you understand the legal and ethical implications of data handling and decision-making in a business context. This is very important when working with data, and creating business requirements.
